  <h1>Built for people who run the work.</h1>

  <p>Wildly Overrun is a show about projects — the finance, the controls, the deals, and the people who actually run them. Capital-intensive, high-stakes, and almost always more complicated than the plan said it would be.</p>

  <p>Every episode starts with a real problem, told by someone who lived it. No panels. No thought leadership. Just the hard-won lessons from owners, operators, financiers, and the people who have managed hundreds of millions — sometimes billions — of dollars worth of work and have the scars to prove it.</p>

  <p>Topics include project finance and controls, contract structure and risk, private equity and infrastructure investment, owner and operator strategy, and the war stories behind projects that blew up in spectacular fashion. Occasional interviews with people who've worked on some of the largest projects in the world.</p>
</div>
